Credit Suisse Moves Farris to Asia as Chief Strategist For F.I.

-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 
2011-02-22T07:35:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/credit-suisse-moves-farris-to-asia-as-chief-strategist-for-f-i-.html
  Credit Suisse Group AG  appointed Ray
Farris as chief strategist for fixed income, Asia Pacific,
according to an e-mailed statement.  Farris, who will continue in his existing role as global
head of foreign exchange strategy, will move to Singapore from  London  as part of his new duties, the statement said.  As chief strategist for fixed income, Asia Pacific, Farris
will be responsible for “developing a cross-asset research
platform covering all Asian fixed income asset classes,” the
statement said.  Farris joined the Swiss bank as an economist in 1998, and
rejoined in 2001 to head the bank’s Asia strategy effort in
rates and foreign exchange, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Katrina Nicholas at 
 knicholas2@bloomberg.net  